title: Is the COVID-19 mortality rate in New York City at least 250x higher than that of Tokyo?
subtitle: A viral tweet from the software engineer John McFee raised questions about social dance measures during the Corona virus epidemic.
author: Jessica Lee
vclaim: On April 25, 2020, the rate of people dying of COVID-19 in New York City was at least 250 times higher than Tokyo - increasing over time.
